<br>
Essence Cullers: MAG/NEC/WIZ Robes and Leggings (edit: I got MAG arms off one of these)<br>
<br>
Feral Amalgams: ROG/WAR Breastplates and Leggings (and Arms?)<br>
<br>
Gale Wolves: SK/CLR Boots, Gloves, Bracers, Helm, Arms<br>
<br>
Glade Stalkers: SHM/BRD Boots, Gloves, Bracers, Helm, Arms<br>
<br>
Guardian Power: CLR/SK Arms, Leggings, Breastplates *Sometimes 2 items*<br>
<br>
Grahl Strongback: Random Arms of any class *Always?*<br>
<br>
Named horse: Random Leggings of any class<br>
<br>
Phase pumas: Random Arms of any class<br>
<br>
Rolling Plains Steeds: NEC/MAG/WIZ Boots, Gloves, Bracers, Helm, Arms<br>
<br>
Spirit Flux Wolves: ROG/WAR, Gloves, Bracers, Helm, Arms (edit: VERY hard, if not impossible to mez - peel of a tank onto one of these if you have more then one or it adds to the fight)<br>
<br>
Spirit Stalker: SHM/BRD Boots, Gloves, Bracers, Helm, Arms (Higher chance then Glade Stalkers)<br>
<br>
Sanguine Kodiak: MNK/ENC Boots, Gloves, Bracers, Helm, Arms<br>
<br>
Sarik the Fang: Drops Arms of any class *Always?*<br>
<br>
Serene Forest Sprites (Green): SHM Arms, Leggings, Breastplates<br>
<br>
Serene Forest Sprites (Yellow): BRD Arms, Leggings, Breastplates<br>
<br>
Sylvan Protectors: MNK/ENC Tunics/Robes and Leggings<br>
<br>
Thifling Sprites: SK/CLR Breastplates and Leggings<br>
<br>
Tranquil Treants: Random Leggings (and Breastplates?) of any class<br>
<br>
Treah Greenroot: Random Breasplates of any class *Always?*<br>
<br>
Wisps: SHM/BRD Breastplates and Leggings<br>
<br>
<br>
Drop list is from Safehouse<br>
<br>
<br>
Warning about Treah... get lots of tanks. They tree has 125k hps and a *VERY* high AC. The fight will last a good 15 minutes but it's a damn fun fight.  Also make sure to clear *ALL* silvan protectors before engaging Treah as he will summon any that remain in the zone to the fight.<br>
<br>
My experience up there as been poor lootwise. 17 trips and I've got mage arms (dropped on my last visit) and the oakleaf girdle. Drops in general are rare compared to the other planes. Still, it's a very easy zone to do.<br>
<br>
Things you MUST remember:<br>
<br>
1-2 Protectors of Growth will spawn every 26-28 minutes and will instantly agro on anyone KoS no matter where they are in the zone. If someone calls &quot;PoGs inc,&quot; stand up immediately or you may get a severe beating. Have someone keep a timer on these bad boys. BTW: They can't be mezzed but root will stick.<br>
<br>
Absolutely, postively *NO* memory wipe spells of *ANY* kind. (mem blur, atone, bard song, etc) These spells will cause the mob to instantly warp and will summon you one by one to your deaths.<br>
<br>
Certain mobs can and will try to gate. (thieflings, wisps, essence cullers, etc) Make sure you have some high lvl chanters armed with a stun, use bash and nuke HARD when it's below 30% or else it will be a mean CR - they summon.<br>
<br>
If a mob gates, immediately call a raid-wide camp. Those who get summoned must do everything in their power to get a /loc or you'll have a hard time finding bodies and you might have to summon their coprses.<br>
<br>
Extra Tips:<br>
<br>
Before you zone into the Plane, make sure to cast Invis on everyone. There is a &quot;whirl of natural energy&quot; guarding the zone in but won't see through invis. Have everyone head to the west wall and start your hunt from there.<br>
<br>
It's REALLY handy to have a non-KoS druid or ranger up with you who can track your kills for you and/or help with any CR. Although they won't get armor drops, druid and ranger spells do drop in the zone.<br>
<br>
